November 22, 1965: Number 1 song on that day

The number 1 song on November 22, 1965 is the best selling or most popular song as resulting from the music charts in the week November 22nd and November 28th. It changes depending on Countries, Music Genres and methodology used to rank the most popular song (for ex., sales, streaming).

November 22, 1965: What was the number 1 song in the USA on that day?

The number 1 song in the USA on November 22, 1965 was I Hear A Symphony by The Supremes, according to the music chart for the week November 22nd and November 28th.

The Supremes - I Hear A Symphony

The Byrds - Turn! Turn! Turn! (To Everything There Is A Season)

What is special about November 22nd?

November 22nd refers to a specific date on the calendar, which is the 22nd day of the month of November. It is a date that occurs annually and is part of the Gregorian calendar, which is widely used around the world.

Over the years several events happened on November 22nd, such as:

2018 - According to the leaning tower at pisa surveillance group, the structure has been leaning less for the past 20 years by 4 cm (1.6 inches)

2017 - Counter-terrorism in georgia. gunfire and explosions are heard in tbilisi, the capital of georgia. this is in response to counter-terrorism operations. three terrorists and one security guard are killed.

2016 - Transasia airways' board decides to dissolve it after tuesday's halt in flights.

What was the calendar for November 1965?

November 1965 followed the same calendar system as the rest of that year and the years surrounding it, with November being the 11th month of the year. This calendar is characterized by 12 months, 365 days in a common year, and 366 days in a leap year, such as 2012.
